article.headline: Austin Peay 71, Belmont 56
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Wes Channels led Austin Peay in a 71-56 win over Belmont on Saturday. Channels scored 19 while Drake Reed added 18 with 11 rebounds. Fernandez Lockett scored another 17. Austin Peay jumped out early, taking the lead in the first half and never trailing. The Governors were up 38-28 at the break. Belmont came back in the second half, finally taking the lead with 12:45 remaining on a 3-pointer by Andy Wicke. But they couldn't hold on. Austin Peay retook the lead for good with 9:17 left as a Lockett free throw made it 48-47. Justin Hare led Belmont with 13 points. Shane Dansby and Matthew Dotson had 10 each. Despite shooting 43 percent from the floor, the same as Austin Peay, Belmont suffered from 24 turnovers.
